<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Mockingbirds
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/TheBirdTribes-Cherokee.html
">The Bird Tribes</A>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cherokee legend about the creation and symbolism of the mockingbird and other birds.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/How_The_Mockingbird_Became_The_Best_Singer-Mayan.html
">How Mockingbird Became The Best Singer</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Maya legend about how the mockingbirds learned to sing.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Mockingbird Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1438435258/natilangofthe-20
">How Mockingbirds Are</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A fascinating book comparing mockingbird imagery and storytelling techniques in the Pima and Papago tribes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0385342489/natilangofthe-20
">Flights of Fancy: Birds in Myth, Legend, and Superstition</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A good book on the meaning of birds in world mythology, including North and South America.
